; organism-mesh.form - extending physical mesh cells to living organisms.
;
; THE ASK
;   Store and extend the swallowed / physical mesh cell idea to any organism,
;   then name the most beneficial scenarios for humanity and Earth as an aware,
;   trusted superorganism we are part of.
;
; THE SHAPE
;   The cell does not own the organism. The organism, steward, community, or
;   ecology sets the membrane. A physical mesh cell can be:
;     - worn, touched, perched nearby, or placed in habitat
;     - swallowed as a pass-through messenger when the organism can consent
;       directly or the clinical/research stewardship is explicit
;     - placed with plants, soils, water, hives, nests, farms, or reefs only
;       at the lowest useful invasiveness
;     - biodegradable or recoverable, and non-replicating
;     - summary-first: raw organism data stays local unless explicitly offered
;
;   The runnable heart is form-stdlib/organism-mesh.fk:
;     om-organism                 organism kind, steward relation, consent, limit
;     om-cell                     carrier, role, invasiveness, transient path, data
;     om-admissible?              consent + invasiveness + noncolonizing + exit
;     om-scenario                 benefit/harm/scale/consent/restoration rows
;     om-vital-scenario?          high-benefit, low-harm, consented, restorative
;     om-earth-awareness-surface? diverse consented trusted restorative receipts
;
; ORGANISM CLASSES
;   human:
;     Direct consent. Swallowed pass-through cells can make sense for hydration,
;     heat stress, medication timing, digestive transit, sleep/recovery, and
;     early infection/inflammation signals. Retained devices are clinical.
;
;   companion animal:
;     Guardian consent. Prefer collars, bedding, water bowl, litter, stable, or
;     near-field habitat cells. Swallowed cells are narrow veterinary/research
;     cases, not the default.
;
;   livestock and working animals:
;     Guardian plus welfare stewardship. Best uses are heat stress, hydration,
;     lameness/motion, feed/water quality, outbreak early warning, and lower
;     antibiotic pressure through earlier care.
;
;   plant, crop, tree, forest:
;     Land/steward consent. Prefer leaf films, bark clips, soil beads, root-zone
;     moisture/nutrient sensing, fungal-network-adjacent sensing, and pollinator
;     corridor receipts. The plant is not a socket; the cell listens lightly.
;
;   soil, water, reef, hive, habitat:
;     Community/ecological stewardship. Prefer passive beads, floats, acoustic
;     listeners, light/temperature/chemistry summaries, and retrieval or
;     biodegradation. Use the field as teacher, not as mine.
;
;   wildlife:
;     Ecological review and local/Indigenous/community stewardship where
;     relevant. Default to field-only observation: acoustic, camera-trap summary,
;     eDNA sampling done by people, habitat sensors. Body contact only with a
;     strong welfare reason and named steward.
;
; BENEFICIAL SCENARIOS
;   1. Heat, hydration, and air early warning
;      Humans, animals, plants, and soils share local heat, water, shade, and air
;      stress summaries. The mesh routes cooling, water, rest, and shade actions
;      before bodies fail.
;
;   2. Regenerative farm and food web care
;      Soil moisture, nutrient cycling, plant stress, pollinator presence,
;      livestock welfare, and human labor fatigue become one consented field.
;      The outcome is less waste, less chemical overuse, better yields, and more
;      life in the soil.
;
;   3. Zoonotic and antimicrobial-resistance early noticing
;      Farms, clinics, shelters, wastewater, and wildlife-habitat boundaries emit
;      derived anomaly receipts instead of raw surveillance. Earlier care reduces
;      spread and lowers indiscriminate antibiotic use.
;
;   4. Watershed and reef vitality
;      Soft cells in streams, wetlands, farms, storm drains, reefs, and coastal
;      zones read temperature, turbidity, pH, oxygen, salinity, and organism
;      presence summaries. The mesh sees stress before collapse and attributes
;      upstream causes without turning every creature into a tracker.
;
;   5. Human wellness as ecological participation
;      Fitness/health is no longer isolated metrics. Sleep, movement, nutrition,
;      heat exposure, indoor air, local food, green space, social care, and
;      ecological state can be read as one vitality surface.
;
;   6. Disaster response and care corridors
;      During fire, flood, heat, smoke, drought, or disease, cells become scouts:
;      passable routes, safe water, shelter load, vulnerable bodies, animal
;      movement, soil/water contamination, and community needs.
;
;   7. Biodiversity corridors that can prove healing
;      Plants, pollinators, birds, soil organisms, water, and human stewards share
;      minimal receipts that show whether a corridor is becoming more alive.
;
; EARTH AWARENESS SURFACE
;   This does not make Earth a centralized patient or a platform someone owns.
;   It makes a consented, plural awareness surface: many organisms and places
;   share enough trusted, derived receipts to notice harm early and coordinate
;   restorative action. The superorganism is not above us. It is the living
;   relation we are already inside, made readable without stripping sovereignty.
;
; PROOF
;   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk \
;     form-stdlib/organism-mesh.fk \
;     form-stdlib/tests/organism-mesh-band.fk
;
; KIN
;   mesh-seed.form, shared-sensing.form, sensor-organ-channel.form,
;   organ-offer.form, channel-interface-consent.form, mesh-health.form,
;   hati-mesh.form, trust-matrix.form.
